description: Outside a real estate office, two men in trench coats and cigars observe a frog in a hat and trench coat sitting behind the wheel of a car, also smoking a cigar. The scene presents an absurd situation where a frog is engaged in driving and seemingly business, contrasting sharply with reality. There is irony in the conversation about selling swampland, a natural habitat for frogs, to another party while a frog is present and perhaps involved. The characters and setting evoke a sense of a clandestine or questionable transaction.
caption: “Well, another sucker just bought twenty acres of swampland.”

other_text.location: Bottom right corner of the comic panel
